  "local_port": 48734,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Which are the companies that hire freshers in Analytics (R programming)?",
  "response": "Several companies across various industries hire freshers for analytics roles that require R programming skills. These companies range from technology giants to consulting firms, financial institutions, and startups. Here\u2019s a list of companies that often hire freshers in analytics with R programming expertise:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Technology Companies**\n- **Google** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n- **Microsoft** (Data Scientist, Data Analyst roles)\n- **Amazon** (Business Analyst, Data Analyst roles)\n- **IBM** (Data Analyst, Data Scientist roles)\n- **Apple** (Data Analyst, Business Intelligence roles)\n\n---\n\n### **2. Consulting Firms**\n- **McKinsey & Company** (Business Analyst, Data Analyst roles)\n- **Boston Consulting Group (BCG)** (Data Analyst, Consultant roles)\n- **Deloitte** (Data Analyst, Data Scientist roles)\n- **PwC (PricewaterhouseCoopers)** (Data Analyst, Consultant roles)\n- **EY (Ernst & Young)** (Data Analyst, Consultant roles)\n- **KPMG** (Data Analyst, Consultant roles)\n- **Accenture** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n\n---\n\n### **3. Financial Institutions**\n- **Goldman Sachs** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n- **JPMorgan Chase & Co.** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n- **Bank of America** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n- **Citi** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n- **Wells Fargo** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n\n---\n\n### **4. E-commerce and Retail**\n- **Walmart** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n- **Target** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n- **Flipkart** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n- **Myntra** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n\n---\n\n### **5. Healthcare and Pharmaceuticals**\n- **Johnson & Johnson** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n- **Pfizer** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n- **Novartis** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n- **Roche** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n\n---\n\n### **6. Startups**\n- **Zomato** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n- **Swiggy** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n- **OYO** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n- **Uber** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n- **Lyft** (Data Analyst, Business Analyst roles)\n\n---\n\n### **7. Analytics and Data Science Companies**\n- **Mu Sigma** (Business Analyst, Data Analyst roles)\n- **Fractal Analytics** (Data Analyst, Data Scientist roles)\n- **Tiger Analytics** (Data Analyst, Data Scientist roles)\n- **LatentView Analytics** (Data Analyst, Consultant roles)\n- **EXL Service** (Data Analyst, Consultant roles)\n\n---\n\n### **8. Education and Training Companies**\n- **Coursera** (Data Analyst roles)\n- **Udemy** (Data Analyst roles)\n- **edX** (Data Analyst roles)\n\n---\n\n### **How to Get Hired as a Fresher**\n1. **Develop R Skills**: Gain proficiency in R programming, data manipulation, visualization (ggplot2, dplyr), and statistical analysis.\n2. **Build Projects**: Create a portfolio of analytics projects using R (e.g., data visualization, predictive modeling).\n3. **Certifications**: Obtain certifications in R programming (e.g., Coursera, DataCamp, edX).\n4. **Internships**: Apply for internships in analytics roles to gain practical experience.\n5. **Networking**: Attend job fairs, connect with professionals on LinkedIn, and join analytics communities.\n\nBy targeting these companies and honing your R programming and analytics skills, you can increase your chances of landing a job as a fresher in analytics.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
